value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: acetyl-CoA + an aralkylamine = CoA + an N-acetylaralkylamine.
Catalysis of the reaction: acetyl-CoA + an arylamine = CoA + an N-acetylarylamine.
Catalysis of the reaction: N-formyl-L-kynurenine + H2O = formate + L-kynurenine.
Catalysis of the reaction: 3'-phosphoadenosine 5'-phosphosulfate + a phenol = adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate + an aryl sulfate.
Catalysis of the reaction: aryl dialkyl phosphate + H2O = dialkyl phosphate + an aryl alcohol.
Catalysis of the reaction: a phenyl acetate + H2O = a phenol + acetate.
Catalysis of the reaction: a phenol sulfate + H2O = a phenol + sulfate.
Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + L-aspartate + L-glutamine = AMP + diphosphate + L-asparagine + L-glutamate.
Catalysis of the reaction: L-asparagine + H2O = L-aspartate + NH3.
Catalysis of the reaction: L-aspartate = beta-alanine + CO2.

definition.value: Note that this term has a MetaCyc pathway reference as the pathway only has a single step.

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: L-aspartate + 2-oxoglutarate = oxaloacetate + L-glutamate.

definition.value: Note that this term has a MetaCyc pathway reference as the pathway only has a single step.

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: L-aspartate + carbamoyl phosphate = N-carbamoyl-L-aspartate + H+ + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + L-aspartate + NH3 = AMP + diphosphate + L-asparagine.
Catalysis of the reaction: L-aspartate + ATP = 4-phospho-L-aspartate + ADP + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: L-aspartate 4-semialdehyde + NADP+ + phosphate = 4-phospho-L-aspartate + H+ + NADPH.
Catalysis of the reaction: bilirubin IXalpha + NAD(P)+ = biliverdin IXalpha + NAD(P)H + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + biotin-carboxyl-carrier protein + CO2 = ADP + phosphate + carboxybiotin-carboxyl-carrier protein.
Catalysis of the reaction: 2 S-adenosyl-L-methionine + dethiobiotin + S(2-) = 2 5'-deoxyadenosine + 2 L-methionine + biotin + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + biotin + L-lysyl-[protein] = AMP + diphosphate + H+ + N(6)-biotinyl-L-lysyl-[protein].
Catalysis of the reaction: P(1),P(4)-bis(5'-nucleosyl)tetraphosphate + H2O = NTP + NMP. Acts on bis(5'-guanosyl)-, bis(5'-xanthosyl)-, bis(5'-adenosyl)- and bis(5'-uridyl)-tetraphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: 3-phospho-D-glyceroyl phosphate = 2,3-bisphospho-D-glycerate.
Catalysis of the reaction: a branched-chain amino acid (L-leucine, L-isoleucine and L-valine) + 2-oxoglutarate = L-glutamate + a 2-oxocarboxylate derived from the branched-chain amino acid.
Catalysis of the reaction: 2 ATP + hydrogencarbonate + NH4+ = 2 ADP + carbamoyl phosphate + 2 H+ + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: 2 ATP + L-glutamine + CO2 + H2O = 2 ADP + phosphate + glutamate + carbamoyl phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: hydrogencarbonate + H+ = CO2 + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction: a secondary alcohol + NADP+ = a ketone + H+ + NADPH.
Catalysis of the reaction: acetyl-CoA + carnitine = (R)-O-acetylcarnitine + CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction: palmitoyl-CoA + L-carnitine = CoA + L-palmitoylcarnitine.
Catalysis of the reaction: 2 hydrogen peroxide = O2 + 2 H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction: 2 catechol + O2 = 2 1,2-benzoquinone + 2 H2O. This reaction catalyzes exclusively the oxidation of catechols (i.e., o-diphenols) to the corresponding o-quinones.

definition.value: GO:0004097 describes oxidation of catechols (i.e., o-diphenols) to the corresponding o-quinones. For monooxygenation of monophenols, consider instead the term 'monophenol monooxygenase activity ; GO:0004503'.

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: a cerebroside 3-sulfate + H2O = a cerebroside + sulfate.
Catalysis of the reaction: chitin + H2O = chitosan + acetate.
Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine + [->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1-](n) = UDP + [->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1-](n+1).
Catalysis of the reaction: acetyl-CoA + choline = acetylcholine + CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + choline = ADP + choline phosphate + 2 H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: an acylcholine + H2O = choline + a carboxylic acid anion.
Catalysis of the reaction: CTP + choline phosphate = diphosphate + CDP-choline.
Catalysis of the reaction: chorismate = prephenate.
Catalysis of the reaction: 5-O-(1-carboxyvinyl)-3-phosphoshikimate = chorismate + phosphate.

Catalysis of the reaction: acetyl-CoA + H2O + oxaloacetate = citrate + CoA, where the acetyl group is added to the si-face of oxaloacetate; acetyl-CoA thus provides the two carbon atoms of the pro-S carboxymethyl group.
Catalysis of the reaction: coproporphyrinogen III + 2 H+ + O2 = 2 CO2 + 2 H2O + protoporphyrinogen IX.
Catalysis of the reaction: 11-deoxycorticosterone = 20-hydroxy-3-oxopregn-4-en-21-al.
Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + creatine = N-phosphocreatine + ADP + 2 H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: a nucleoside cyclic phosphate + H2O = a nucleoside phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: nucleoside 2',3'-cyclic phosphate + H2O = nucleoside 2'-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: a nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphate + H2O = a nucleoside 5'-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: 3',5'-cyclic AMP + H2O = AMP + H+.
Catalysis of the reactions: 3',5'-cyclic AMP + H2O = AMP + H+ and 3',5'-cyclic GMP + H2O = GMP + H+; this activity is activated by binding to calcium-bound calmodulin.
Catalysis of the reaction: nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphate + H2O = nucleoside 5'-phosphate; catalytic activity is increased in the presence of cGMP.
Catalysis of the reaction: nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphate + H2O = nucleoside 5'-phosphate; catalytic activity is decreased in the presence of cGMP.
